    <intro>&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style="background-color: #ffff00;"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="background-color: #ffffff; color: #800080;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;P&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="background-color: #ffffff; color: #800080;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;lease post your reflections on the&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color: #800080;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt; following &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color: #800080;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;question to this Discussion Forum:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style="color: #800080;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;span style="color: #008000;"&gt;&lt;span style="color: #008000;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;img style="float: left; margin-left: 10px; margin-right: 10px;" alt="Discussion Graphic - multicolored heads with gear thought balloons" src="@@PLUGINFILE@@/LTA-EI-Discussionicon.jpg" height="67" width="86" /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color: #000000;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Reflection Question:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;em&gt; Considering the &lt;span class="autolink"&gt;principles of Explicit Instruction (below)&lt;/span&gt;, which one of these principles are you most interested in applying to your instruction? Why?&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color: #008000;"&gt;&lt;span style="color: #008000;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style="color: #000000;"&gt;&lt;em&gt; &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style="color: #000000;"&gt;&lt;em&gt; &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Principles of Explicit Instruction:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Learning is focused on meaningful and critical content.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;What students are learning is precisely defined.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Skills are sequenced logically.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Students know what they will be learning and why.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Teacher provides organized and structured instruction using the following techniques: review, explanation, demonstration/modeling, examples/nonexamples, and scaffolded practice.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;div class="O1"&gt;&lt;span style="color: #008000;"&gt;&lt;strong class="O1"&gt;To enhance your learning: &lt;span style="color: #000000;"&gt;We encourage you to read and reply to other participants' reflections. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style="color: #000000;"&gt;Checking back to this forum frequently, or choosing to receive e-mails for this forum, can assist in this process.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style="color: #008000;"&gt;Reminder: Instructions for Posting:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;(1) Click on the "Add a new topic"&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;button&lt;/strong&gt;. &lt;em&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;(2) Type your information in the subject and message boxes.&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;em&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;(3) Save and share your post.&lt;/strong&gt; Remember to choose if you want e-mails of posts from this forum, and then &lt;strong&gt;click on the "Post to Forum" button.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="color: #008000;"&gt;&lt;span style="color: #000000;"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
